content: Amazing app. Also got the hard copy $5 foldout map as a backup. Both are awesome. The loc feature helps find the trails.
Does not work on Galaxy S6. Asked for a refund.
Wonderful app if you are visiting St John in the US I. Highly recommended!
Fantastic! Best $2 I spent on this trip.

Using this app on the trails of St. John now.  Works great without an internet connection.  Tells you exactly where the trails are, where you are on the trail and gives great descriptions of the trails.  Also information about beaches, snorkeling, and much more.  Well worth the charge!!!  Works great on my HTC 10.
Really helpful for finding and navigating along trails. The G.P.S. locator really completes the functionality. This has been an essential tool
The app crashes when I try to display maps. It has the number of information features which link back to bad links at the st. John's site. It needs to be updated to match the new site.
It used to work.  Now it crashes my Samsung S4 pretty much anytime I try to load the map or find my location on  the map.  Don't pay for this app.

This is an awesome app if visiting St.John, USVI. I love how it can be used in offline mode so that my cell phone is not hit with roaming charges and it works when there is no connection. There is enough information to keep a person busy for weeks exploring the beautiful island. I hope more is added to this app such as restaurants and updated regularly. Well worth the $1.99!  Not as much information as the book but much more convenient! With a waterproof phone case I can even look where we want to go next while snorkeling :)
